":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7313,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/30\/man-forgiven-thirsty-dog\/","url_meta":{"origin":5460,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Animals: Man forgiven for mercy to thirsty dog","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 30, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA\u00a0man suffered from thirst while he was walking on a journey. When he found a well, he climbed down into it and drank from it. Then he came out and saw a dog lolling its tongue\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/23\/prophet-observed-wasala-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":5460,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: The Prophet continuously fasted, Muslims may not","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would observe continuous fasting during the month of Ramadan and so did the people, but he prohibited them. It was said, \u201cYou are continuously fasting.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, I am not like you, for I am\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":